TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

\{image("1050s6p11.gif", height => 512, width => 512);\}

Let \[f(x) = x+1\quad\hbox{and}\quad g(x) = -x-1.\]

$BR

In the Figure above, match the colors of the graphs in this Figure
with the functions given.  Enter y for yellow, b for blue, r
for red,  and g for green, as
appropriate.

$BR

$BR\{ ans_rule(3) \} \(y=f(x) \)
EOT
ANS(str_cmp("b"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR\{ ans_rule(3) \} \(y = g(x)\)
EOT
ANS(str_cmp("r"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR\{ ans_rule(3) \} \(y = (f\circ g)(x))\)
EOT
ANS(str_cmp("y"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR\{ ans_rule(3) \} \(y = (g \circ f)(x))\)
$BR
EOT
ANS(str_cmp("g"));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD The Maple code to generate these graphs is
$BR

\(f:=x+1; \)$BR
\(g:=-x-1; \)$BR
\(plot([f,g,subs(x=f,g),subs(x=g,f)],x=-2..2,y=-3..3,discont = true, 
thickness=2);
\)

EOT



